  "prompt": "Have Tam Bra (Tamil Brahmin) started wearing silk undergarments?",
  "response": "The question of whether Tamil Brahmins (Tam Brahmins) have started wearing silk undergarments is quite specific and niche. Generally, silk garments are typically reserved for outer clothing due to their luxurious and expensive nature. There is no widely available information indicating a trend among Tamil Brahmins or any other community toward wearing silk undergarments specifically.\n\nTamil Brahmins often adhere to traditional practices, including wearing silk sarees and dhotis during religious ceremonies and festivals due to the auspicious nature of silk in Hindu culture. However, the choice of undergarments is usually influenced by comfort, practicality, and personal preference, much like in other communities.\n\nFor accurate and up-to-date information, it would be best to consult sources or individuals within the community or look into specific cultural studies or trends.",
